geland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Whatton in the Vale, Nottinghamshire,England":"Whatton, Nottinghamshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Melton Mowbray, Leicestershire, England":"Melton Mowbray, Leicestershire, England","Whatton, Nottinghamshire, England":"Whatton, Nottinghamshire, England"},"en":{"1299–after 1340":"1299–after 1340","1299–1340":"1299–1340","–1310":"–1310","1297–1359":"1297–1359","1330–1369":"1330–1369","1345–Male":"1345–Deceased","1274–1336":"1274–1336","–1313":"–1313","1330":"1330","1297":"1297","1274":"1274","1340":"1340","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1359":"1359","1336":"1336","1369":"1369","1313":"1313","1345":"1345","1299":"1299","1453":"1453","1310":"1310","after 1340":"after 1340","about 1330":"about 1330","Feb 1313":"February 1313","3 Mach 1336":"1336","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Sproxton, Leicestershire, England":"Sproxton, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","Whatton in the Vale, Nottinghamshire,England":"Whatton, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom","Melton Mowbray, Leicestershire, England":"Melton Mowbray, Leicestershire, England","Whatton, Nottinghamshire, England":"Whatton, Nottinghamshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Walton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of numerous places called Walton, which are named with Old English <i>walh</i> ‘foreigner, Briton, serf’ (genitive plural <i>wala</i>), <i>wald</i> ‘woodland’, <i>wall</i> ‘wall’, or <i>wælla</i> ‘well, spring, stream’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’.","History: George Walton (1741–1804) signed the Declaration of Independence. He was born in Prince Edward County, VA, whither his grandfather had emigrated from England in 1682. He moved to Savannah, GA, and became governor of GA and a prominent jurist."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":16,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":29,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":38,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes de Walton was born in 1299, in Whatton, Nottinghamshire, England as the daughter of Richard III Whatton , Lord of Whatton and Agnes Palmer. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Sir John Brabazon. She died after 1340, in Sproxton, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1299–after 1340":"1299–pärast 1340","1299–1340":"1299–1340","–1310":"–1310","1297–1359":"1297–1359","1330–1369":"1330–1369","1345–Male":"1345–Surnud","1274–1336":"1274–1336","–1313":"–1313","1330":"1330","1297":"1297","1274":"1274","1340":"1340","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1359":"1359","1336":"1336","1369":"1369","1313":"1313","1345":"1345","1299":"1299","1453":"1453","1310":"1310","after 1340":"pärast 1340","about 1330":"umbes 1330","Feb 1313":"veebruar 1313","3 Mach 1336":"1336","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Sproxton, Leicestershire, England":"Sproxton, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Whatton in the Vale, Nottinghamshire,England":"Whatton, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Melton Mowbray, Leicestershire, England":"Melton Mowbray, Leicestershire, England","Whatton, Nottinghamshire, England":"Whatton, Nottinghamshire, England"},"fi":{"1299–after 1340":"1299–1340 jälkeen","1299–1340":"1299–1340","–1310":"–1310","1297–1359":"1297–1359","1330–1369":"1330–1369","1345–Male":"1345–Kuollut","1274–1336":"1274–1336","–1313":"–1313","1330":"1330","1297":"1297","1274":"1274","1340":"1340","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1359":"1359","1336":"1336","1369":"1369","1313":"1313","1345":"1345","1299":"1299","1453":"1453","131